cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.PL

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it discusses the modelling of multivariate densities using Gaussian mixture models, which is a core component of many machine learning applications. The paper also discusses the use of the Expectation Maximisation (EM) and k-means training algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category as it discusses the use of multi-threading to achieve faster training of the GMMs. 

The cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is also a possibility as GMMs are commonly used in computer vision applications such as image segmentation and object recognition. 

The cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses techniques to improve numerical stability and modelling accuracy. 

Finally, the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses the implementation of the GMMs in the C++ language and the use of the Armadillo C++ linear algebra library.
